The issue is in `App.tsx`. While the logic to load the username exists, the actual Dashboard component is currently being passed `currentUser.email` directly in the JSX, which overrides the username you loaded.

I will fix this by passing the calculated `displayName` (or the formatted name) to the Dashboard instead of the raw email.

