export default App;

The issue is that while `AuthScreen` is saving the username to the database, `App.tsx` isn't listening for that database record—it's only checking the Google Authentication profile (which can be slow to update) or defaulting to the email address.

I am adding a specific listener in `App.tsx` that watches your user profile in the database. As soon as `AuthScreen` saves the username (during sign up), this listener will trigger and instantly update the dashboard to show the username instead of the email.

# Updated files:

## App.tsx

Added a `useEffect` hook to listen to the `users/{uid}` Firestore document. This ensures that `userDisplay` is updated with the custom `username` field from the database as soon as it is created or changed, fixing the issue where the email was shown.

